Sentencas: Metallic Pd and PdO electrodes were prepared by using Pd and PdCl2 slurries, respectively, and their electrochemical performance as a cathode for oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells was evaluated by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) and direct current polarization (DC polarization).
Titulo: Comparative study of Pd and PdO as cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical activity of metallic Pd was much higher than that of PdO for the reaction of oxygen reduction; below the decomposition temperature, a thin layer of PdO formed on the surface of metallic Pd electrode, which increased its polarization resistance.
Titulo: Comparative study of Pd and PdO as cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The decomposition temperature of PdO decreased from 810 to 750 degrees C as oxygen partial pressure decreased from 20 to 5 kPa, and was further lowered under the influence of the applied current during DC polarization test.
Titulo: Comparative study of Pd and PdO as cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The charge transfer resistance of PdO increased by decreasing oxygen partial pressure, while that of metallic Pd was less sensitive to it.
Titulo: Comparative study of Pd and PdO as cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
